
== Quick startup guide ==

1. Configure:
> ./do configure-auto

2. Build:
> ./do build

3. Install into '/opt/notary_@VERSION@':
> ./do install

4. Add the '/opt/notary_@VERSION@/bin' to PATH:
> export PATH="/opt/notary_@VERSION@/bin:$PATH"

5. Create cryptographic keys:
> notary_@VERSION@_default_create_keys

6. Create record database:
> notary_@VERSION@_default_create_db

7. Start daemons:
> notary_@VERSION@_default_start_daemons

8. Stop daemons:
> notary_@VERSION@_default_stop_daemons

o. Backup database:
> notary_@VERSION@_default_backup_db

o. Run scan:
> notary_@VERSION@_default_run_scan


== 'do' script options ==

 * configure-auto:
  * automatically detect dependencies;
  * use default values for installation and configuration;
 * configure-ui: start a nice curses UI for configuration;
 * build: ...;
 * clean: ...;
 * install: ...;
